## 2. Core Brand Palette

The Vrvish palette is premium, stark, and highly legible. It is a strictly disciplined two-tone blue system, designed to reflect the tension and harmony between human stability and machine execution.

| Role | Colour Name | Hex Code | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Foundation (Human)** | **Vrvish Navy** | `#00142A` | The deep base. Text, massive background blocks, primary logos, the Horse logo, and wordmarks. Communicates stability, structure, and human legacy. |
| **Navy Surface** | **Navy Surface** | `#0a1e32` | Slightly elevated navy for surfaces (buttons, inputs, cards). Use on navy theme. |
| **Navy Elevated** | **Navy Elevated** | `#0f2440` | Dropdowns, popovers, overlays. One step above surface. |
| **Navy Subtle** | **Navy Subtle** | `#152a48` | Subtle backgrounds, scrollbar thumb, tertiary surfaces. |
| **Accent (Machine)** | **Vrvish Azure** | `#007FFF` | The spark. The Venn-V dot over the `i`, primary Call to Action buttons, active states, laser-thin divider lines. Communicates speed, electricity, and the machine engine. |
| **Contrast** | **Pure White** | `#FFFFFF` | Backgrounds, the negative space elements (the hidden V in the horse and the Venn-V dot), and typography on Navy backgrounds. |
| **Secondary Support** | **Slate Grays** | e.g. `#8A8A9E` | Secondary/UI text, subtle component borders, inactive states. |

> **Design Principle**: Vrvish Navy grounds the brand in reality (infrastructure). Electric Azure spikes the brand into the future (augmentation). Stick strictly to these blues; introducing reds or greens dilutes the Enterprise-grade discipline.

## Web design switch.  
We give users the option of a dark mode (navy) or a light white mode

